Back in the 80s ASU and Tempe were very conservative.  I returned for a PhD in 2021 as an old Gen X guy.  The place has gone far left and woke for politics relative to the 80s.  This song reminds me of the modern youth culture in Tempe - very woke with blurred sexual identities across the progressive "rainbow" spectrum.  As a moderately conservative Catholic, I am fully aware I am an old guy out-of-place with that scene.  So, I just walk around campus as if HR has a drone flying over me and focus on my dissertation and courses.  But that song really hits the campus vibe these days - a far cry from the 80s with duets like Olivia Newton John and Cliff Richard in "Suddenly".
